  "prompt": "What is reliance jio?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio, officially known as Reliance Jio Infocomm Limited, is a telecommunications company based in India and a subsidiary of Reliance Industries Limited. Launched in September 2016, Jio revolutionized the Indian telecom market by offering affordable 4G LTE services, which included voice calls, text messaging, and high-speed internet access.\n\nKey features of Reliance Jio include:\n\n1. **4G LTE Network**: Jio was one of the first companies to offer nationwide 4G LTE coverage in India, focusing on delivering high-speed internet services.\n\n2. **Affordable Pricing**: Jio gained massive popularity by introducing disruptive pricing models, including free voice calls and low-cost data plans, which significantly reduced the cost of mobile data in India.\n\n3. **Wide Range of Services**: In addition to mobile telecom services, Jio offers various digital services, including JioTV, JioCinema, JioSaavn (now JioMusic), and JioCloud, among others.\n\n4. **Rapid Subscriber Growth**: Within a short period, Jio gained hundreds of millions of subscribers, becoming one of the largest mobile network operators in India.\n\n5. **Infrastructure Development**: The company invested heavily in building telecommunications infrastructure, including fiber optic networks, to support its services.\n\n6. **Impact on the Market**: Jio's entry into the market led to increased competition, resulting in reduced prices and improved services from other telecom providers.\n\nOverall, Reliance Jio has played a significant role in transforming the telecommunications landscape in India, making internet access more affordable and widespread.",
